---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import AztecPattern from '../../components/decorative/AztecPattern.astro';
import GeometricBorder from '../../components/decorative/GeometricBorder.astro';
import CircuitFeather from '../../components/CircuitFeather.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="City-States of Mirador"
  description="The competing urban enclaves in the world of Mirador, each with their own approach to capability licensing."
>
  <!-- Hero Section with Pattern -->
  <div class="relative py-24 bg-primary-800">
    <AztecPattern pattern="tribute" opacity={0.15} color="#A63D2F" className="hero-pattern" />
    
    <div class="container mx-auto px-8 relative z-10">
      <div class="flex items-center space-x-4 mb-6">
        <CircuitFeather severity="moderate" size="lg" animated={true} />
        <h1 class="text-4xl font-heading font-bold text-white tracking-wider">City-States of Mirador</h1>
      </div>
      <p class="text-xl text-neutral-200 max-w-2xl">
        In a world fragmented by competing visions of utopia, these urban enclaves license 
        capabilities from Toltec Corporation to build their distinct societies.
      </p>
      <GeometricBorder type="horizontal" color="accent" className="mt-8 w-32" />
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Main Content -->
  <div class="bg-primary-900 py-16">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-8">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-heading font-bold mb-6 text-accent-400">The New Geography</h2>
        <GeometricBorder type="horizontal" color="accent" className="mb-6 w-24" />
        
        <p class="text-lg mb-6 text-neutral-200">
          In the aftermath of the Great Dissolution, when nation-states crumbled under their own inefficiencies, 
          a new type of urban organization emerged: city-states. Each founded by tech billionaires and corporate 
          consortiums, these urban enclaves offer distinct visions of how society should function, all powered 
          by Toltec's attention-processing capabilities.
        </p>
        
        <!-- Mirador -->
        <div class="bg-primary-800 p-8 rounded-lg border border-primary-700 my-12 relative overflow-hidden">
          <AztecPattern pattern="codex" opacity={0.1} color="#1A237E" className="city-pattern" />
          <div class="relative z-10">
            <div class="flex items-center mb-6">
              <CircuitFeather severity="critical" size="md" className="mr-4" />
              <h3 class="text-2xl font-heading font-medium text-white">Mirador</h3>
            </div>
            
            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-8 mb-6">
              <div>
                <h4 class="text-sm uppercase tracking-wider text-neutral-400 mb-2">Founder</h4>
                <p class="text-neutral-200">John Lawson, Toltec CEO</p>
              </div>
              <div>
                <h4 class="text-sm uppercase tracking-wider text-neutral-400 mb-2">Core Principle</h4>
                <p class="text-neutral-200">Attention as Currency</p>
              </div>
              <div>
                <h4 class="text-sm uppercase tracking-wider text-neutral-400 mb-2">Tier</h4>
                <p class="text-neutral-200">Tier 1 (Primary Publisher)</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            
            <p class="text-neutral-200 mb-4">
              Mirador is the original capability developer and home to Toltec Corporation. It controls the core 
              attention-processing technologies that power all other city-states. Within its gleaming spires, citizens 
              participate in an economy where every glance and moment of focus has monetary value.
            </p>
            
            <p class="text-neutral-200">
              As the primary capability provider, Mirador maintains strict control over how its technologies are used 
              and licensed throughout the network of city-states. The reconciliation processes designed to ensure 
              compliance serve as Mirador's control mechanism over its peers.
            </p>
            
            <div class="mt-6">
              <a href="/technical/publishers?mode=technical" class="text-secondary-400 hover:text-secondary-300 transition-colors text-sm">Technical details →</a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        
        <!-- New Valencia -->
        <div class="bg-primary-800 p-8 rounded-lg border border-primary-700 my-12 relative overflow-hidden">
          <AztecPattern pattern="grid" opacity={0.1} color="#2E6E4E" className="city-pattern" />
          <div class="relative z-10">
            <div class="flex items-center mb-6">
              <CircuitFeather severity="moderate" size="md" className="mr-4" />
              <h3 class="text-2xl font-heading font-medium text-white">New Valencia</h3>
            </div>
            
            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-8 mb-6">
              <div>
                <h4 class="text-sm uppercase tracking-wider text-neutral-400 mb-2">Founder</h4>
                <p class="text-neutral-200">Elena Cruz, Former Tech CEO</p>
              </div>
              <div>
                <h4 class="text-sm uppercase tracking-wider text-neutral-400 mb-2">Core Principle</h4>
                <p class="text-neutral-200">Entrepreneurial Innovation</p>
              </div>
              <div>
                <h4 class="text-sm uppercase tracking-wider text-neutral-400 mb-2">Tier</h4>
                <p class="text-neutral-200">Tier 2 (Secondary Publisher)</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            
            <p class="text-neutral-200 mb-4">
              New Valencia is a bustling commercial hub that pushes the limits of its capability licensing agreements. 
              Known for its entrepreneurial spirit, the city-state has become famous for developing innovative applications 
              of Toltec's core capabilities, sometimes walking a fine line between compliance and violation.
            </p>
            
            <p class="text-neutral-200">
              The city is constantly in flux, with new ventures launching daily and experimental attention markets that 
              operate in regulatory gray areas. Nextla agents like Silas Hale frequently find themselves mediating 
              disputes between New Valencia and Toltec over capability usage.
            </p>
            
            <div class="mt-6">
              <a href="/technical/publishers?mode=technical" class="text-secondary-400 hover:text-secondary-300 transition-colors text-sm">Technical details →</a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        
        <!-- Arcadia -->
        <div class="bg-primary-800 p-8 rounded-lg border border-primary-700 my-12 relative overflow-hidden">
          <AztecPattern pattern="flow" opacity={0.1} color="#A63D2F" className="city-pattern" />
          <div class="relative z-10">
            <div class="flex items-center mb-6">
              <CircuitFeather severity="severe" size="md" className="mr-4" />
              <h3 class="text-2xl font-heading font-medium text-white">Arcadia</h3>
            </div>
            
            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-8 mb-6">
              <div>
                <h4 class="text-sm uppercase tracking-wider text-neutral-400 mb-2">Founder</h4>
                <p class="text-neutral-200">Marcus Wei, Arts Foundation Director</p>
              </div>
              <div>
                <h4 class="text-sm uppercase tracking-wider text-neutral-400 mb-2">Core Principle</h4>
                <p class="text-neutral-200">Creative Expression</p>
              </div>
              <div>
                <h4 class="text-sm uppercase tracking-wider text-neutral-400 mb-2">Tier</h4>
                <p class="text-neutral-200">Tier 2 (Secondary Publisher)</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            
            <p class="text-neutral-200 mb-4">
              Arcadia is an arts-focused enclave that frequently runs afoul of its capability licensing agreements. 
              The city-state prioritizes creative expression above all else, leading to magnificent cultural achievements 
              but also significant capability imbalances.
            </p>
            
            <p class="text-neutral-200">
              The Spectacle capability is frequently overused here, resulting in more manifestations than any other city-state. 
              Residents view these manifestations as a form of public art, while Toltec sees them as dangerous compliance violations.
            </p>
            
            <div class="mt-6">
              <a href="/technical/publishers?mode=technical" class="text-secondary-400 hover:text-secondary-300 transition-colors text-sm">Technical details →</a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        
        <!-- Nexus -->
        <div class="bg-primary-800 p-8 rounded-lg border border-primary-700 my-12 relative overflow-hidden">
          <AztecPattern pattern="tribute" opacity={0.1} color="#FFC107" className="city-pattern" />
          <div class="relative z-10">
            <div class="flex items-center mb-6">
              <CircuitFeather severity="minor" size="md" className="mr-4" />
              <h3 class="text-2xl font-heading font-medium text-white">Nexus</h3>
            </div>
            
            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-8 mb-6">
              <div>
                <h4 class="text-sm uppercase tracking-wider text-neutral-400 mb-2">Founder</h4>
                <p class="text-neutral-200">Diana Chen, AI Pioneer</p>
              </div>
              <div>
                <h4 class="text-sm uppercase tracking-wider text-neutral-400 mb-2">Core Principle</h4>
                <p class="text-neutral-200">Technological Advancement</p>
              </div>
              <div>
                <h4 class="text-sm uppercase tracking-wider text-neutral-400 mb-2">Tier</h4>
                <p class="text-neutral-200">Tier 3 (Tertiary Publisher)</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            
            <p class="text-neutral-200 mb-4">
              Nexus is a technology development center that creates new applications of capabilities within strict 
              compliance frameworks. The city-state maintains the most stable and balanced capability usage, making it 
              Toltec's most reliable partner.
            </p>
            
            <p class="text-neutral-200">
              Where other city-states push boundaries, Nexus works within them to develop technologies that enhance human 
              potential. Their advanced reconciliation systems often detect and correct imbalances before they manifest, 
              making manifestations rare within their borders.
            </p>
            
            <div class="mt-6">
              <a href="/technical/publishers?mode=technical" class="text-secondary-400 hover:text-secondary-300 transition-colors text-sm">Technical details →</a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        
        <!-- Outland -->
        <div class="bg-primary-800 p-8 rounded-lg border border-primary-700 my-12 relative overflow-hidden">
          <AztecPattern pattern="grid" opacity={0.1} color="#A63D2F" className="city-pattern" />
          <div class="relative z-10">
            <div class="flex items-center mb-6">
              <CircuitFeather severity="critical" size="md" className="mr-4" />
              <h3 class="text-2xl font-heading font-medium text-white">Outland</h3>
            </div>
            
            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-8 mb-6">
              <div>
                <h4 class="text-sm uppercase tracking-wider text-neutral-400 mb-2">Founder</h4>
                <p class="text-neutral-200">Enrique, Former Toltec Engineer</p>
              </div>
              <div>
                <h4 class="text-sm uppercase tracking-wider text-neutral-400 mb-2">Core Principle</h4>
                <p class="text-neutral-200">Liberation from Attention Economy</p>
              </div>
              <div>
                <h4 class="text-sm uppercase tracking-wider text-neutral-400 mb-2">Tier</h4>
                <p class="text-neutral-200">Unlicensed (Resistance)</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            
            <p class="text-neutral-200 mb-4">
              Outland isn't a recognized city-state but rather a collection of settlements outside the official network. 
              Led by Enrique, a former Toltec engineer, these communities reject the attention economy entirely, using 
              modified and hacked versions of capabilities without licensing agreements.
            </p>
            
            <p class="text-neutral-200">
              Toltec considers Outland a dangerous piracy operation, while Outland residents view themselves as freedom 
              fighters liberating humanity from attention-based control. Reconciliation agents like Silas often find 
              themselves caught between these competing worldviews.
            </p>
            
            <div class="mt-6">
              <a href="/narrative/silas?mode=narrative" class="text-accent-400 hover:text-accent-300 transition-colors text-sm">Read Silas's story →</a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout> 